# Trivy False Positives / Accepted Risks
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Each entry below suppresses a specific finding that has been reviewed
# and accepted as a known risk or false positive.
#
# FORMAT: CVE-YYYY-NNNNN or vulnerability ID
# REVIEW: All entries must be reviewed quarterly
# LAST REVIEWED: 2026-06-22
#
# HOW TO USE:
# If Trivy reports a vulnerability that is:
#   - Not applicable to your use case (e.g., a Windows-only vuln on Linux)
#   - Already mitigated by other controls
#   - A false positive (scanner misidentified the version)
# Add it here with a comment explaining WHY it's accepted.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never suppress a finding without documenting the justification.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Example (uncomment if needed):
# CVE-2024-XXXXX  # Not applicable: affects Windows only, we run Linux containers
